Here's the PlantUML component diagram for the `libremfg_getting-started` deployment architecture:

```plantuml
@startuml libremfg_getting-started
!theme plain

component "Docker Host" {
    component "Dgraph" as dgraph
    component "InfluxDB" as influxdb
    component "EMQX (MQTT Broker)" as emqx
    component "Grafana" as grafana {
        component "Pareto Panel Plugin" as pareto
        component "MultiStat Panel Plugin" as multistat
    }

    component "Libre Platform" as libre {
        component "Libre Core" as core
        component "Libre Admin UI" as adminui
        component "GraphQL Gateway" as gateway
        component "GraphQL PubSub" as pubsub
        component "Workflow Engine" as workflow
    }

    component "PackML Simulator" as packml
}

dgraph --> gateway : GraphQL queries
influxdb --> grafana : Time-series data
emqx --> pubsub : MQTT events
pubsub --> gateway : Federated schema
core --> adminui : Serves UI
adminui --> gateway : API calls
gateway --> core : Federated schema
workflow --> gateway : Federated schema
packml --> emqx : MQTT telemetry
pareto --> influxdb : Queries data
multistat --> influxdb : Queries data

note right of libre
  Deployed as Docker containers
  managed via docker-compose.yml
end note

@enduml
```